This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the limitations of graph neural networks and proposes a method to overcome them. Additionally, the paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed method through experiments. 

The paper also involves solving graph problems, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Furthermore, the paper mentions the use of GNNs for computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
